title: Movie Review...Venom
body: (3.5/5) Not as bad as recent reviews but could have been a lot better, a lot. There were several issues that I had with the movie. Number one…the filmed could and should have been longer. The plot played like I expected but some things could have been drawn out more. I would have placed the film into 4 acts expanding what was already within the film. I wanted to expand on the mission to space, the astronaut and the crash (like the 90s cartoon with a combination of the film The Astronauts Wife). I would have expanded Eddy story…his job, his fiancee and ultimately him meeting Venom…then moved to him getting use to the symbiote. Secondly the design of Venom is something I would have changed from the voice to visually. He was definitely to glossy and his voice changed several times in the film….not sure if that was done intentionally or not. My third and final issue was the script. There were times where I felt the dialogue fell flat. I’m not sure if this was done with the intention of being funny or this was a result of bad writing or that rushed feeling I got with the film. Lastly, not really a issue, but Riz should have had more screen time. They are definitely on to something with this film and this was an worthwhile foundation in my opinion. Journalist Eddie Brock is trying to take down Carlton Drake, the notorious and brilliant founder of the Life Foundation. While investigating one of Drake’s experiments, Eddie’s body merges with the alien Venom – leaving him with superhuman strength and power. Twisted, dark and fueled by rage, Venom tries to control the new and dangerous abilities that Eddie finds so intoxicating (google.com).

Word Count: 
Warnings: Fluff 
Spending time at each other’s flat
Oversized jumpers and fuzzy...
body:
Fall HC’s

Pairing: Peter Parker x GN Reader

Word Count:

Warnings: Fluff

  • Spending time at each other’s flat
  • Oversized jumpers and fuzzy socks
  • Adding multiple Halloween stations to your Pandora way before October
  • Forcing him to take cliché couple pictures with you
  • Walking around Central Park
  • Starbucks
  • Some evenings the two of you will just sit in your room with the window open
  • Enjoying the comfortable silence
  • Honestly, no matter what you were doing with him; you wouldn’t trade it for anything. You were so grateful for that boy!
  • Sitting in your car after school waiting out the rain
  • Both of you are drenched
  • Convincing him to climb in the backseat to cuddle with you to keep warm
  • Watching Peter attempt to climb over the seat was hilarious
  • He ended up kicking you in the face
  • You were laughing too hard to care
  • You struggled as well. You ended up falling on him
  • The two of you were laughing so hard your faces turned red
  • After the laughter had died down, you took your place on Peter’s lap. Your head resting on his chest.
  • That boy’s face was so red!
  • The rhythm of his heartbeat quickened slightly
  • Smiling to yourself because you’re the cause of it
  • The rain had finally stopped so you unfortunately had to take ‘P’ home.
  • You loved when he wore jumpers or flannels with a beanie
  • He looked so good.
  • Always hyping your boy up
  • “Damn, Parker! “You better go!”

October:

  • Peter is so in for it
  • It’s only the third day of October when you start screaming “This Is Halloween” whenever you see him
  • Halloween movies
  • Doesn’t matter how shitty they are
  • Pete doesn’t really understand your obsession with the films
  • He’s happy that you’re so passionate about something. Even if it’s a little odd.
  • You had asked him to make cookies with you
  • You had forgotten about them and they ended up burnt
  • So you went to the store and bought two packs of the ghost and pumpkin sugar cookies.
  • ‘P’ wasn’t a fan of them
  • The face he made when he took a bite out of one was priceless
  • You totally took a picture of it and set it as your lock screen
  • He was so pissed
  • “Y/N! Please take that off!”
  • “You gotta catch me first, Benjamin!”
  • That set him off
  • “Oh, shit. “I’m screwed.”

title: Only friends (1/7)  [Peter Parker x Reader]
body:
Summary: Peter Parker was many things, but Y/N didn’t expected him to be the love of her life (fluff, little angst)

Words: 450 +/-

Warnings: none

*Prologue* *Part 2* *Part 3* *Part 4*  *Part 5* *Part 6*

Peter Parker was a traitor.

Some say that betrayal is a forgivable thing, that the one who love, forgive. Forgive is my ass. Whoever forgives is a God. 

He was looking at me with that sad face, with his brown eyes and curved lips in a lovely beak as I clearly saw the proof that he had indeed betrayed me.

We were in an awesome friendship for many years, and I never expected to be stabbed in the back that way, but the proof was right before my eyes, in “Continue the third episode.”

He had watched the first three episodes of the tenth season of Supernatural without me, and it was at that moment that I saw our relationship, which was once considered perfect, crumble.

“Y/N … Please believe me, it’s not what you’re thinking …”

“It’s right in front of me.”

“I can explain …”

“Explain what?” I asked quietly, my voice filled with grief. "I trusted you, Parker. How can you do this to me?”

“Let me explain, please!” He clasped his hands in supplication, making me let out a weary sigh. I shrugged, finally giving up. There was no denying a request in front of that face. I shook my head forward, encouraging him to speak. 

"You remember the storm that fell on Thursday, don’t you?” Of course I remembered, after all, I took so much rain that a mini pond had formed in the pocket of my jacket. “So, as soon as you left, the energy was gone. I had read all the Destiel fanfics you did in my library. I was without internet and in total boredom. I had downloaded the three episodes to see the next day, since we had literature class, but then, in an impulsive act, I saw it… I swear it wasn’t purposeful, Y/N … Please, I’m sorry.”

“My heart is broken.” I said taking my hand dramatically to my chest.

"I can fix it, love. I swear to you, it will never happen again.” He promised, stretching his little finger in my direction. I stared at his stretched finger, seriously considering whether or not to seal that promise, but my indecision made Peter’s sad pouting fall even more, and my heart isn’t made of iron, so I gathered our little pinkies and sealed the promise. I smiled as I felt his arms wrapping me in a clumsy hug, feeling my chest heat up with that act.

On that boring Sunday, we spent the whole afternoon creating a thousand theories trying to figure out who God was, and in the end, we were both wrong.

Sometimes life has these plot twist and you just have to go with it.

Taglist: @tokoyamisstuff, @imrllybored

He was looking at me with that sad face, with his brown eyes and curved lips in a lovely beak as I clearly saw the proof that he had indeed betrayed me.

We were in an awesome friendship for many years, and I never expected to be stabbed in the back that way, but the proof was right before my eyes, in “Continue the third episode.”

He had watched the first three episodes of the tenth season of Supernatural without me, and it was at that moment that I saw our relationship, which was once considered perfect, crumble.

“Y/N … Please believe me, it’s not what you’re thinking …”

“It’s right in front of me.”

“I can explain …”

“Explain what?” I asked quietly, my voice filled with grief. "I trusted you, Parker. How can you do this to me?”

“Let me explain, please!” He clasped his hands in supplication, making me let out a weary sigh. I shrugged, finally giving up. There was no denying a request in front of that face. I shook my head forward, encouraging him to speak. 

"You remember the storm that fell on Thursday, don’t you?” Of course I remembered, after all, I took so much rain that a mini pond had formed in the pocket of my jacket. “So, as soon as you left, the energy was gone. I had read all the Destiel fanfics you did in my library. I was without internet and in total boredom. I had downloaded the three episodes to see the next day, since we had literature class, but then, in an impulsive act, I saw it… I swear it wasn’t purposeful, Y/N … Please, I’m sorry.”

“My heart is broken.” I said taking my hand dramatically to my chest.

"I can fix it, love. I swear to you, it will never happen again.” He promised, stretching his little finger in my direction. I stared at his stretched finger, seriously considering whether or not to seal that promise, but my indecision made Peter’s sad pouting fall even more, and my heart isn’t made of iron, so I gathered our little pinkies and sealed the promise. I smiled as I felt his arms wrapping me in a clumsy hug, feeling my chest heat up with that act.

On that boring Sunday, we spent the whole afternoon creating a thousand theories trying to figure out who God was, and in the end, we were both wrong.

Sometimes life has these plot twist and you just have to go with it.

summary:
Spider Sense
Used mostly as a way to detect impending danger, Spider-Man’s spider sense is a reflex that allows him to react to...
body:
Spider Sense

Used mostly as a way to detect impending danger, Spider-Man’s spider sense is a reflex that allows him to react to threats quickly. While not perfect, it’s saved ‘ol webhead from being shot or sucker punched innumerable times.

It can also detect passive threats, such as a foes that mean to do Spidey or others harm in his vicinity, before they strike. In some cases, as pictured above, friends and foes are able to transmit messages to Spider-Man via his spider sense.

This ability is usually indicated on panel with squiggled lines haloing Spidey’s head.
